Class.rdfs:label: Advanced Wireless Service Base Station
Class.skos:definition: no definition available

Class.rdfs:label: Active Satellite
Class.skos:definition: A satellite carrying a station intended to transmit or retransmit radiocommunication signals. (RR)

Class.rdfs:label: Advanced Wireless Service
Class.skos:definition: Advanced Wireless Service (AWS) is the collective term the FCC uses for innovative fixed and mobile terrestrial wireless services using bandwidth that is sufficient for the provision of a variety of applications, including those using voice and data (such as internet browsing, message services, and full-motion video) content. The services provided by AWS licensees are limited only by the Fixed and Mobile designation of the spectrum we allocate for AWS and the services rules we ultimately adopt for the bands.

Class.rdfs:label: Aeronautical Earth Station
Class.skos:definition: • with one or more stations of the same kind by means of one or more reflecting satellites or other objects in space

Class.rdfs:label: Allocation
Class.skos:definition: Allocation contains the allocation of a specific frequency band to a specific radiocommunication service.

Class.rdfs:label: Allotment
Class.skos:definition: Allotment is a group of frequencies given to a subordinate organisation for local management, for specific types of emissions, at a certain location, and for a specified period of time.

Class.rdfs:label: Army-Navy/Portable Radio Communications
Class.skos:definition: The Harris AN/PRC-117G delivers breakthrough wideband data speed and legacy narrowband performance in a form factor 30% smaller and 35% lighter than any other currently in field. The manpack is also the industry’s first and only tactical radio with NINE Suite B encryption. This frees sovereign nations to securely interoperate with U.S., NATO and regional tactical partners and eliminates the time and cost of maintaining two separate radio systems.

Class.rdfs:label: Assignment
Class.skos:definition: Assignment is the XML root for all parameters of a system of assignments

Class.rdfs:label: Base Station
Class.skos:definition: Base Station: A land station in the land mobile service. (RR) (NTIA Definition Sept 2015)

Class.rdfs:label: Cable TV Relay Service
Class.skos:definition: Cable Television Relay Service (CARS) stations are point-to-point or point-to-multipoint microwave systems used by cable and other MVPD operators. CARS stations cannot be used to distribute programming directly to subscribers. Sec. 78.18 lists the frequency assignments for CARS……Relay services let callers use an assistant who transfers messages back and forth. If you don't have a TTY unit or TDD, you can use a telephone relay service to communicate by phone with someone who is deaf or hard of hearing. ... The person placing the call accesses TRS from any TTY or standard phone by calling 7-1-1.

Class.rdfs:label: Earth Station
Class.skos:definition: Earth Station: A station located either on the Earth's surface or within the major portion of the Earth's atmosphere and intended for communication:
• with one or more space stations; or

Class.rdfs:label: Electronic Warfare
Class.skos:definition: (joint) Military action involving the use of electromagnetic and directed energy to control the electromagnetic spectrum or to attack the enemy.

Class.rdfs:label: FederalAffiliation
Class.skos:definition: This is a type of affiliation. If federal, the item belongs to or is controlled by a federal organization

Class.rdfs:label: Federal Base Station
Class.skos:definition: In the NTIA policies, this is a base station that has a federal affiliation.

Class.rdfs:label: Frequency Band
Class.skos:definition: A frequency band is an interval in the frequency domain, delimited by a lower frequency and an upper frequency. The term may refer to a radio band or an interval of some other spectrum. The frequency range of a system is the range over which it is considered to provide satisfactory performance, such as a useful level of signal with acceptable distortion characteristics. A listing of the upper and lower limits of frequency limits for a system is not useful without a criterion for what the range represents.

Class.rdfs:label: Frequency Maximum
Class.skos:definition: This is the maximum value for a frequency range

Class.rdfs:label: Frequency Minimum
Class.skos:definition: This is the minimum value for a frequency range

Class.rdfs:label: Frequency Range
Class.skos:definition: (1) A group of frequencies in the electromagnetic spectrum that are assigned by regulatory agencies for a particular purpose. Also called a "frequency band. (2) A group of frequencies that occur naturally such as the audio spectrum.

Class.rdfs:label: Frequency Requestor
Class.skos:definition: In the policies, this is some system making a request for spectrum frequency

Class.rdfs:label: General Dynamics
Class.skos:definition: General Dynamics is a global aerospace and defense company.

Class.rdfs:label: GeographicalZone
Class.skos:definition: The five main latitude regions of the Earth's surface comprise geographical zones, divided by the major circles of latitude. The differences between them relate to climate.

Class.rdfs:label: Joint Tactical Radio System
Class.skos:definition: The Joint Tactical Radio System (JTRS) aimed to replace existing radios in the American military with a single set of software-defined radios that could have new frequencies and modes (“waveforms”) added via upload, instead of requiring multiple radio types in ground vehicles, and using circuit board swaps in order to upgrade. JTRS has seen cost overruns and full program restructurings, along with cancellation of some parts of the program.

Class.rdfs:label: Local TV Transmission Service
Class.skos:definition: Local Television Transmission Service (LTTS) stations are available for communications common carriers to provide service to television broadcast stations, network entities, cable system operators and cable network entities. Fixed point-to-point, temporary fixed and mobile operations are permitted in LTTS.

Class.rdfs:label: Memorandum of Understanding
Class.skos:definition: A memorandum of understanding (MOU) can be used to establish Interoperability between federal entities and non-federal public safety licensees.

Class.rdfs:label: Non-Federal
Class.skos:definition: This is a type of affiliation. If non-federal, the item belongs to or is controlled by a commercial or non-federal entity

Class.rdfs:label: Non-Federal Base Station
Class.skos:definition: In the NTIA policies, this is a base station that has a non-federal affiliation, e.g., commercial

Class.rdfs:label: Primary
Class.skos:definition:
"In the NTIA policies, a spectrum requester may have a primary or secondary status. Primary indicates that the requester can operate without interference. Secondary indicates that the requester is permitted to operate on a non-interference basis only.
"

Class.rdfs:label: Radio Frequency
Class.skos:definition: Radio frequency (RF) refers to the rate of oscillation of electromagnetic radio waves in the range of 3 kHz to 300 GHz, as well as the alternating currents carrying the radio signals. This is the frequency band that is used for communications transmission and broadcasting.

Class.rdfs:label: Radio Frequency System
Class.skos:definition: Complex element RFSystem describes the association of one or several Transmitters, Receivers and Antennas as they are assembled to form a system on a platform; it can also include the specific modes which are allowed or technically possible in this assembly.

Class.rdfs:label: Radio Transmitter
Class.skos:definition: In electronics and telecommunications, a transmitter or radio transmitter is an electronic device which produces radio waves with an antenna. The transmitter itself generates a radio frequency alternating current, which is applied to the antenna. When excited by this alternating current, the antenna radiates radio waves.

Class.rdfs:label: Satellite
Class.skos:definition: A body which revolves around another body of preponderant mass and which has a motion primarily and permanently determined by the force of attraction of that other body. (RR)

Class.rdfs:label: Site
Class.skos:definition: This is a geographical type with geo/loc and other information where activities can occur and where spectrum can be restricted
